41    /**
42    * Red-Black tree-based implementation of BidiMap where all objects added
43    * implement the <code>Comparable</code> interface.
44    * <p>
45    * This class guarantees that the map will be in both ascending key order
46    * and ascending value order, sorted according to the natural order for
47    * the key's and value's classes.
48    * <p>
49    * This Map is intended for applications that need to be able to look
50    * up a key-value pairing by either key or value, and need to do so
51    * with equal efficiency.
52    * <p>
53    * While that goal could be accomplished by taking a pair of TreeMaps
54    * and redirecting requests to the appropriate TreeMap (e.g.,
55    * containsKey would be directed to the TreeMap that maps values to
56    * keys, containsValue would be directed to the TreeMap that maps keys
57    * to values), there are problems with that implementation.
58    * If the data contained in the TreeMaps is large, the cost of redundant
59    * storage becomes significant. The {@link DualTreeBidiMap} and
60    * {@link DualHashBidiMap} implementations use this approach.
61    * <p>
62    * This solution keeps minimizes the data storage by holding data only once.
63    * The red-black algorithm is based on {@link java.util.TreeMap}, but has been modified
64    * to simultaneously map a tree node by key and by value. This doubles the
65    * cost of put operations (but so does using two TreeMaps), and nearly doubles
66    * the cost of remove operations (there is a savings in that the lookup of the
67    * node to be removed only has to be performed once). And since only one node
68    * contains the key and value, storage is significantly less than that
69    * required by two TreeMaps.
70    * <p>
71    * The Map.Entry instances returned by the appropriate methods will
72    * not allow setValue() and will throw an
73    * UnsupportedOperationException on attempts to call that method.
74    *
75    * @since 3.0 (previously DoubleOrderedMap v2.0)
76    * @version $Id$
77    */
